msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The prefork MPM implements a non-threaded, preforking Web server. It makes "
"the Web server behave similarly to Apache version 1.x. In this version it "
"isolates each request and handles it by forking a separate child process. "
"Thus problematic requests cannot affect others, avoiding a lockup of the Web "
"server."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: apache2.xml:1391
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"While providing stability with this process-based approach, the prefork MPM "
"consumes more system resources than its counterpart, the worker MPM. The "
"prefork MPM is considered the default MPM for Unix-based operating systems."
msgstr ""

